  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Critical support for the restoration of livelihoods of smallholder farmers in Balochistan and Pakistan Administered Kashmir</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to enable targeted farmers with tools to cope with the negative effects of the cold wave emergency in Balochistan and Pakistan Administered Kashmir. FAO will use CERF funds to provide 1,500 women with a conditional cash grant for kitchen gardening and 12,707 households with highly nutritious compound feed package for their livestock. Nearly 25,000 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within 3 months.</narrative>
  </description>
